The paper involves the use of deep learning-based AI software for the detection of glaucoma from stereoscopic optic disc photographs, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The study also evaluates the diagnostic performance of the AI system, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the comparison of the AI system's performance with that of ophthalmologists and optometrists, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
